5:
A full month has passed—I believe
that concludes our contract.
12:
As per our terms, I'll have you fetch
the dog woman now.
14:
I won't take no for an answer—you
know how I get when someone
breaches a contract.
18:
There's no need for such bloodlust.
I'll fight you willingly, Little Lady.
21:
Thank you, Alk. Your work here is
done.
26:
...No killing, you hear? That goes for
both of you.
30:
Haha. Please, we're just going to
have a friendly bout, that's all.
35:
Pathetic statements like that make
my blood boil—or are you trying to
goad me into breaching the terms
of my contract?
37:
No matter. I won't kill you. I'll simply
break you instead.
41:
Oho, "break?" I'm afraid you'll find me
a tougher cookie to crack than that,
my dear.
44:
But of course, we won't be having
our fight here.
52:
Part of me didn't believe she'd follow
through with the whole thing—she
did what I told her for a whole
month!
57: Indeed. Because that's all she knows.
60:
She doesn't know how to engage
with people in any capacity other
than through a binding contract.
62:
Rules are absolute for her. That's
why her temper flares so much
when someone breaks them.
64:
I'm not here to render
judgment—that's simply the way
she was born. Nothing more to it.
69:
Still... Living a life like that sounds...
suffocating.
73:
It seems like you've gotten to know
her very well, Alk.
77: Not that I particularly wanted to...
83:
So you chose to play fair? Odd. I
thought you the unscrupulous type.
87:
Trust me, if there were a loophole in
my contract, I would have already
reduced you to dust.
91:
Haha. Communication isn't really
your strong suit, is it?
94:
What use is there talking to those
who are too stupid to act in their
own interest?
98:
If you did, perhaps you'd learn to
understand them.
101:
A waste of time. Did you do the
same, I wonder? Talk things through
with a revenge-hungry foe on the
battlefield?
105:
No. I cut them down. But that was a
long, long time ago.
108:
Well then, perhaps you'd like to
reminisce?
112:
Show me who you really are. Let me
see the beast within!
116: Just this one time, I'll indulge you.
126:
Are you mocking me? What is the
meaning of this?
129:
You saw the path forward, did you
not? The path to greatness—the way
to become the most powerful
warrior!
131:
How... How could THIS be all you can
muster?
135:
I'm afraid it is. This is the full extent of
my power.
137:
These were your orders, were they
not? To become the beast, to lose
my humanity. Well, I did.
140:
I reverted back to who I once was—a
creature without even a reason to
kill. With no will of my own.
150:
When last we fought, you
demonstrated such overwhelming
power... This time, you are barely a
shadow of your former self.
152:
You mean to say that your strength
waxes and wanes along with your
emotional state?
155:
Indeed. When we last fought, I was
filled with the determination to
protect something important to me.
158:
A cause I was willing to fight for.
Blood-stained though I may
emerge, a light awaited me at the
end.
160: That is why I was strong.
164:
How trivial. What does any of that
matter? You have the aptitude to
attain true greatness, and yet...
166:
You...
You refuse to shed your humanity!
169:
Correct. It's not in my nature to be
inhuman.
174:
The path you've chosen... is truly an
arduous one.
177:
I would choose it every time over the
path you walk. You, who grasped
true power and let it wither away!
180:
What is this "light" you spoke of? If
you had it again, would you be able
to regain the power you once had?
183:
It's hard to put into words. Suffice to
say, the light can be a person.
Perhaps you already have someone
like that in your life?
187:
Hmph. Him? Everything he does
irritates me...
190:
Listen here.
I will surpass you, no matter what.
194:
To do that, I'll need you to bring back
the beast I fought before. That's an
order.
197: Well now. That's quite the task.
200: You'd do well not to forget it.
205:
My, my... You've got your hands full
babysitting this one, don't you, Alk?
207: I honestly don't know how you do it.
